==English==

===Etymology===
From its capability of ''looking down'' from the intercepting aircraft to the ground and then ''shooting down'' the enemy.

===Alternative spellings===
'''look-down shoot-down''', '''look-down/shoot-down''' (''also, non-standardly, without hyphens'')

===Adjective===
'''look-down, shoot-down'''
# Describing a phased-array radar powerful enough to pick aircraft out of ground [[clutter]] from high [[altitude]].